-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Aldar Properties and Bank of Sharjah Gain
-- B y   D a n a   E l   B a l t a j i   a n d   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2011-12-28T10:33:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/persian-gulf-stocks-aldar-properties-and-bank-of-sharjah-gain.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose 2.1
percent, the most in almost two months, to 1,346.47 at the 2
p.m. close in the emirate, trimming this year’s decline to 17
percent. Abu Dhabi’s ADX General Index gained 0.6 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols follow company names.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR UH) climbed the most since
Oct. 30, rising 3.7 percent to 84 fils. The board of Abu Dhabi’s
biggest developer by market value plans to meet today to discuss
the possible sale of assets.  Bank of Sharjah (BOS)   advanced 2.6 percent to 1.96
dirhams, the highest level since March 2010. The United Arab
Emirates bank bought back 3.68 million shares yesterday and has
regulatory approval to purchase a further 96 million shares, it
said in a statement to the  Abu Dhabi  bourse today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
